Motional Stark Effect
MSE System on MAST-U
A multichannel MSE system is employed on
MAST-U which is used to measure the pitch angle
of the magnetic field. These measurements
constrain equilibrium reconstruction codes and
measure edge current density and q profiles.
These are important parameters for understanding
and mitigating Edge Localised Modes (ELMs).

There are added challenges when employing MSE
in a spherical tokamak:
The magnetic field strength is lower.
Curvature of the magnetic field is larger.
MSE spectrum suffers from spectrum broadening
and overlapping pi/sigma lines due to:
Variation in B and Es over the collection
volume.
Beam velocity distribution causes Doppler
broadening.
Birefringent photoelastic modulators (PEM) and polarizer encode
polarisation state as modulated intensity signal, as optical fibres
do not preserve light polarization.
